---
---

<html lang="en">
    <head>
        <meta charset="utf-8" />
        <title>About Strudel-app</title>
        <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
        <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
        <link
            href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,100..1000;1,9..40,100..1000&family=Space+Mono:ital,wght@0,400;0,700;1,400;1,700&display=swap"
            rel="stylesheet"
        />
        <style>
            :root {
                --c-bg: #000000;
                --c-base: #0a0a0a;
                --c-panel: #121212;
                --c-border: #262626;
                --c-accent: #ffffff;
                --c-text: #f5f5f5;
                --c-muted: #a3a3a3;
                --f-mono: "Space Mono", "JetBrains Mono", "Fira Code", monospace;
                --f-ui: "DM Sans", "Inter", system-ui, sans-serif;
            }

            body {
                background: var(--c-bg);
                color: var(--c-text);
                font-family: var(--f-ui);
                line-height: 1.6;
                margin: 0;
                padding: 40px 20px;
                min-height: 100vh;
                scrollbar-width: thin;
                scrollbar-color: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.3) rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            }

            ::-webkit-scrollbar {
                width: 6px;
                height: 6px;
            }
            ::-webkit-scrollbar-track {
                background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            }
            ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb {
                background: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.3);
                border-radius: 3px;
            }
            ::-webkit-scrollbar-thumb:hover {
                background: rgba(0, 229, 255, 0.6);
            }

            .container {
                max-width: 800px;
                margin: 0 auto;
                background: var(--c-base);
                border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
                border-radius: 8px;
                padding: 40px;
                box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
            }

            h1 {
                color: var(--c-accent);
                font-size: 2.5rem;
                margin-top: 0;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
                font-weight: 700;
                letter-spacing: -0.5px;
            }

            h2 {
                color: #fff;
                font-size: 1.5rem;
                margin-top: 40px;
                margin-bottom: 20px;
                border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
                padding-bottom: 10px;
            }

            h3 {
                color: #fff;
                font-size: 1.1rem;
                margin-top: 25px;
            }

            p {
                margin-bottom: 20px;
                font-size: 1.05rem;
            }

            .lead {
                font-size: 1.25rem;
                color: #fff;
                font-weight: 500;
                margin-bottom: 30px;
            }

            code {
                font-family: var(--f-mono);
                background: var(--c-panel);
                padding: 2px 6px;
                border-radius: 4px;
                font-size: 0.9em;
                color: #ffffff;
            }

            pre {
                background: var(--c-panel);
                padding: 20px;
                border-radius: 6px;
                border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
                overflow-x: auto;
                font-family: var(--f-mono);
                font-size: 0.95em;
                line-height: 1.5;
                color: #d4d4d4;
            }

            .button-grid {
                display: grid;
                grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(300px, 1fr));
                gap: 20px;
                margin-top: 30px;
            }

            .button-card {
                background: var(--c-panel);
                border: 1px solid var(--c-border);
                border-radius: 6px;
                padding: 20px;
            }

            .btn-name {
                font-family: var(--f-mono);
                color: var(--c-accent);
                font-weight: 700;
                font-size: 1rem;
                margin-bottom: 10px;
                display: inline-block;
                background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);
                padding: 4px 8px;
                border-radius: 4px;
                letter-spacing: 1px;
            }

            .back-link {
                display: inline-flex;
                align-items: center;
                gap: 8px;
                color: var(--c-muted);
                text-decoration: none;
                font-family: var(--f-mono);
                font-weight: 700;
                font-size: 0.9rem;
                margin-bottom: 30px;
                transition: color 0.2s;
                letter-spacing: 1px;
            }

            .back-link:hover {
                color: var(--c-accent);
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <div class="container">
            <a href="/" class="back-link">← BACK TO DAW</a>

            <h1>What is Strudel?</h1>
            <p class="lead">
                Strudel is a live coding environment for creating music using
                JavaScript.
            </p>

            <p>
                It is a web-based port of <strong>TidalCycles</strong>,
                utilizing the Web Audio API to schedule precise rhymic patterns
                and synthesize audio directly in your browser. With Strudel, you
                write code to sequence drums, trigger synthesizers, slice audio
                samples, and apply complex musical transformations in real-time.
            </p>

            <h2>How to Use The Pattern Editor</h2>
            <p>
                The core of this application is the Pattern Editor. Here you
                write standard JavaScript expressions using the Strudel DSL
                (Domain Specific Language).
            </p>

            <p>
                The most basic pattern uses the <code>s()</code> function to trigger
                sounds by name. The mini-notation inside the quotes determines the
                rhythm.
            </p>

            <pre><code>// A basic four-on-the-floor drum beat
s("bd hh bd hh")

s("bd hh bd hh").fast(2)

s("[bd hh bd hh, bd sd bd sd]")</code></pre>

            <p>
                Whenever you want to hear your changes, simply press the <strong
                    >▶ PLAY</strong
                > button. The engine will seamlessly crossfade your new code into
                the active audio stream.
            </p>

            <h2>DAW Controls Reference</h2>

            <div class="button-grid">
                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">▶ PLAY</span>
                    <p>
                        Evaluates the code currently in the Pattern Editor and
                        schedules the audio. If audio is already playing, it
                        will seamlessly crossfade to the new pattern on the next
                        cycle.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">■ STOP</span>
                    <p>
                        Instantly zeroes the volume and stops the Strudel rhythm
                        scheduler. Stops the active cycle.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">BPM CONTROLS</span>
                    <p>
                        Adjusts the global Tempo in Beats Per Minute. You can
                        use the up/down nudge arrows, or click the number to
                        type an exact value. <em
                            >Note: 1 Strudel cycle = 4 Beats</em
                        >.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">LOOP (∞ / 1)</span>
                    <p>
                        By default, patterns loop infinitely (∞). If set to
                        "Once" (1), the engine will play exactly one full cycle
                        and then automatically stop. Great for rendering exact
                        loops.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">↑ LOAD</span>
                    <p>
                        Opens a native file browser to load a `.strudel` or
                        `.txt` file from your device straight into the Pattern
                        Editor.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">↓ CODE</span>
                    <p>
                        Downloads the current contents of your Pattern Editor to
                        your device as a `.strudel` file. Use this to save
                        patches you really like to share or load later.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">● REC / ■ STOP REC</span>
                    <p>
                        Clicking REC starts capturing an MP4/WebM recording. It
                        mixes the master audio feed combined with the 60fps
                        video feed from the Oscilloscope canvas. Clicking STOP
                        REC will instantly download the video to your device.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <div class="button-card">
                    <span class="btn-name">CLEAR</span>
                    <p>
                        A quick-action button that destroys the text inside the
                        code editor and deletes the `localStorage` draft cache.
                        Destructive action.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </body>
</html>
